# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 16 (solution): Green-Kubo cross-check of the liquid-Al self-diffusion
# coefficient from the velocity autocorrelation function (VACF).
#
# This computes D at a single temperature by an independent route: instead of
# the slope of the mean-squared displacement (Einstein, diffusion.lmp), it
# integrates the VACF,  D = (1/dim) * integral_0^inf <v(0).v(t)> dt.  The two
# estimates should agree within the (larger) statistical scatter of the VACF.

units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p

variable T equal 1200

# build, melt, and equilibrate the liquid exactly as in diffusion.lmp
lattice fcc 4.045
region box block 0 8 0 8 0 8
create_box 1 box
create_atoms 1 box
pair_style eam/fs
pair_coeff * * Al_mm.eam.fs Al
timestep 0.002

velocity all create 2000.0 5783 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
fix melt all npt temp 2000.0 2000.0 0.2 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
run 10000
unfix melt
fix equi all npt temp ${T} ${T} 0.2 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
run 20000
unfix equi

# production: NVT (fixed volume, temperature pinned at the target) and
# accumulate the velocity autocorrelation function
reset_timestep 0
fix nvt all nvt temp ${T} ${T} 0.2
compute vacf all vacf
# VACF(t) for the figure (and for plotting/integrating in LAMMPS-GUI)
fix outvacf all ave/time 1 1 2 c_vacf[4] file vacf_${T}.dat
# running Green-Kubo integral; spacing between samples is 1 step = dt
fix vec all vector 1 c_vacf[4]
variable D equal (1.0/3.0)*dt*trap(f_vec)
thermo 100
thermo_style custom step temp c_vacf[4] v_D

# The VACF decays within a fraction of a picosecond (with a negative "cage"
# rebound typical of a dense liquid), so its integral converges within ~1 ps.
# A single-time-origin VACF becomes noisy at long times, and integrating into
# that noisy tail spuriously inflates D, so we take the integral over the
# converged decay window only.
run 500
variable Dgk equal $(v_D)     # freeze the converged Green-Kubo value
unfix vec
variable D delete             # v_D referenced fix vec, which is now gone
thermo_style custom step temp c_vacf[4]
# keep running a little longer only to record the decayed VACF tail for the plot
run 2500

print "Green-Kubo D(${T} K) = ${Dgk} Ang^2/ps = $(v_Dgk*1.0e-8:%.3e) m^2/s"
print "(compare with the MSD/Einstein value from diffusion.lmp at the same T)"
